tooltip_properties.description: Once anchored to the terrain, a drill rod can be inserted into a well head to begin drilling a well. In order to drill effectively a drill rod should be driven by a rotary table and forced downward toward the terrain. A continuous supply of drilling slurry must be provided through the drill rod via a swivel, and the saturated drilling slurry extracted from the well head fluid port.
tooltip_properties.short_description: A well head for oil drilling.

logic_node.label: Anchor
logic_node.description: Extend / retract piles to anchor the well head to the terrain, allowing for a new well to be drilled. The well head must be close to the terrain (~1m) and upright (+-30 degrees) to be anchored. Unanchoring the well will reset any drilling progress made.

logic_node.label: Is Anchored
logic_node.description: Returns true when the well head is anchored to the terrain.

logic_node.label: Drill Depth
logic_node.description: Returns the depth of an attached drill rod in meters.

logic_node.label: Well Depth
logic_node.description: Returns the depth of the drilled well in meters.
